(2939, 'Hostel Baščaršija', 'hostel-baščaršija', 40, 1209, '<p>All units feature a balcony with views of the Old Town on one side, or the Orthodox church on the other. Ironing facilities and a desk come with each room. Guests have access to 5 shared bathrooms,women''s room&nbsp;<br><br>A bar and a restaurant serving local, traditional and international food are just steps away from the Baš Baščaršija Hostel. A grocery shop is 20 metres away, while a green market can be found 100 m.<br><br>A tourist agency run by the property is 200 metres away and offers excursions, rafting and paragliding, as well as trips to Mostar, Srebrenica and others. The Main Bus and Train Stations are 2 km from the property.&nbsp;<br><br>Hostel Rooms: 25.<br><br>General<br>Free parking for guests hostel,24-hour front desk, Newspapers, Terrace, Non-smoking rooms,&nbsp;women''s room,Design hotel, Luggage storage, Ski storage, Designated smoking area, Shared kitchen.<br><br>Activities<br>Golf course (within 3 km), Fishing, Skiing, Hiking, Horse riding, Ski school, Evening entertainment.<br><br>Services<br>Tour desk, Fax/photocopying, Shuttle service (surcharge), Airport shuttle (surcharge), Shared lounge/TV area.Free parking for guests hostel<br><br>Policies of Hostel Baš Baščaršija<br>PetsPets are not allowed.<br><br>One child under 3 years stays free of charge when using existing beds.<br>There is no capacity for cots in the room.<br>Any type of extra bed or child''s cot/crib is upon request and needs to be confirmed by management.<br>Supplements are not calculated automatically in the total costs and will have to be paid for separately during your stay.<br><br>Cash onlyThis property only accepts cash payments.<br><br>Credit cards are only needed to&nbsp;guarantee your booking.<br><br>Check-in &nbsp; &nbsp;09:00 - 23:00 hours<br>Check-out &nbsp;09:00 - 10:00 hours<br><strong><a>Important information</a><br>Please note that the reception is located 200 metres from the property at the following address: Jaroslava Cernija Street 1.</strong><br><br><strong>Baščaršija</strong><strong>&nbsp;is Sarajevo’s old bazaar and the historical and cultural center of the city. Baščaršija was built in the 15th century when Isa-Beg Isaković founded the town.&nbsp;</strong><br><strong>Baščaršija is located on the north bank of the river Miljacka in the municipality of Stari Grad (Old Town)</strong>&nbsp;in the very heart of the city.&nbsp;<br>Just steps away from Hostel Bas Bascarsija are famous restaurants, cafes, gift shops, and some of the most beautiful examples of Ottoman architecture. Best pastries and coffee is served less than 60 meters from our door step.<br>!!!!!!!ROOMS PRICING STARTS AT 10 EUROS PER NIGHT!!!!<br></p>', '43.85996194875006', '18.43020647764206', 'Hostel Baš Baščaršija is located in the central core of the Baščaršija old town, just steps away from several significant sights, cultural and historic monuments, night clubs and restaurants. The hostel offers free Wi-Fi. ', 0, '', 1, '', 25, 19, '60', '0', 1, 0, 1, 1, 'hostel bascarsija', '', '', 2, 'Hostel Baščaršija', 'hostel-baščaršija-en', '', '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
