(3528, 'Imaret i musafirhana', 'imaret-i-musafirhana', 91, 1199, '<p>U kompleksu Sahat-kule nalazio se Gazi Husrev-begov imaret, besplatna kuhinja za službenike objekata njegovog vakufa, studente i sirotinju. U istom ansamblu bila je i musafirhana... <br></p><p>...kuća uređena za putnike namjernike, u kojoj se moglo besplatno tri dana jesti i konačiti. Za vrijeme austrougarske okupacije musafirhana je prvobitno služila kao vojni magazin, a kasnije kao oficirski klub, koji je nazvan Aeroplan. <br> <br> Danas su tu privatna pekara, slastičarna i nacionalni restoran s lijepom baštom. U ovom restoranu možete uživati u tradicionalnim bosanskim slatkim specijalitetima, od kojih Vam preporučujemo baklavu, hurmašice, ružice, tufahije i kadaif.  <br></p>', '43.85921349848677', '18.42844158411026', 'U kompleksu Sahat-kule nalazio se Gazi Husrev-begov imaret, besplatna kuhinja za službenike objekata njegovog vakufa, studente i sirotinju.', 753, '127,6,107', 1, 'Atrakcija ,Istorija,Čaršija,Baščaršija', 44, 15, '19', '0', 1, 0, 1, 1, 'imaret i musafirhana', 'atrakcija ,istorija,carsija,bascarsija', 'u kompleksu sahat-kule nalazio se gazi husrev-begov imaret, besplatna kuhinja za sluzbenike objekata njegovog vakufa, studente i sirotinju.', 1, 'Imaret and Musafirhana', 'imaret-i-musafirhana-en', '<p></p>The Clock-Tower complex also consisted of imaret and musafirhana. Imaret\n was a public kitchen established for employees of the Ghazi \nHusrev-Bey’s waqf, students and the hungry. Musafirhana was a house \ndesigned for visitors to Sarajevo.<div>It provided three-day overnight accommodation and meals free of charge. \nDuring the Austro-Hungarian period, it was first used as a military \nstorage place, and later turned into an Officer’s Club called \n"Aeroplan”. Today, it is a national restaurant with a nice outdoor cafe \nand delicious traditional cakes such as baklava (layered pastry with \nnuts soaked in syrup), hurmasica (a date-shaped pasty soaked in a sweet \nsyrup sauce), ruzica (round layered pastry with nuts soaked in syrup), \ntufahija (stewed apples with a walnut filling) and kadaif (crunchy \nkanafeh pastry with sweet syrup).&nbsp;<br><div><div><div><div><p><br></p></div></div></div></div></div>', 'The Clock-Tower complex also consisted of imaret and musafirhana.', 'imaret and musafirhana', 'u kompleksu sahat-kule nalazio se gazi husrev-begov imaret, besplatna kuhinja za sluzbenike objekata njegovog vakufa, studente i sirotinju.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3529, '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0, '#Atrakcija ,#Istorija,#Čaršija,#Baščaršija', 0, 18, '', '0', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', '', '', 1, '', '-en', '', '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3530, 'Tašlihan', 'tašlihan', 91, 481, '<p>Tašlihan je podignut 1543. godine kao zadužbina Gazi Husrev-bega. Od ovog kamenog hana, koji je nekada imao šadrvan, džamiju, dvorište... <br></p><p>...i oko dvorišta dućane i magaze, nakon nekoliko požara, u kojima je oštećen, danas su ostale samo zidine u bašti hotela "Europa".  <br></p>', '43.858484378989274', '18.427964150905606', 'Tašlihan je podignut 1543. godine kao zadužbina Gazi Husrev-bega. Od ovog kamenog hana, koji je nekada imao šadrvan, džamiju, dvorište...', 422, '59,-10,107', 1, '#Baščaršija,#Čaršija,#Istorija,#Kultura,#Atrakcija', 81, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'taslihan', '', 'taslihan je podignut 1543. godine kao zaduzbina gazi husrev-bega. od ovog kamenog hana, koji je nekada imao sadrvan, dzamiju, dvoriste...', 1, 'Taslihan', 'tašlihan-en', '<p></p>Taslihan was built in 1543 as the Ghazi Husrev-Bey’s waqf. It had a \nfountain, mosque, yard, shops and storage rooms.It was severely damaged \nin several fires that struck Sarajevo.<div><br><div>Nowadays, only wall remains are visible and rest at the Europa Hotel’s outdoor café.<br><div><div><p><br></p></div></div></div></div>', 'Taslihan was built in 1543 as the Ghazi Husrev-Bey’s waqf. It had a fountain, mosque, yard, shops and storage rooms.', 'taslihan', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3531, 'Kuršumlija medresa', 'kuršumlija-medresa', 37, 1558, '<p>Kuršumlija medresa je visoka vjerska škola, Gazi Husrev-begova zadužbina iz 1537. godine, posvećena dobrotvorovoj majci Seldžuki, kćerki sultana Bajazita II. U svoje vrijeme bila je pandan najpoznatijim evropskim univerzitetima.  <br></p><p>Medresu Seldžukiju narod je prozvao Kuršumlijom zbog njenog olovnog krovnog pokrivača (tur. kuršum – olovo). Ima centralni atrij s trijemom i stupovima, dvanaest učionica i salu za predavanja, dershanu. <br> <br> Na centralnom mjestu helenističkog dvorišta je šadrvan. Objekt je građen od kamena. Svaka prostorija pokrivena je zasebnom kupolom i ima vlastiti kamin i odžak. Služi kao umjetnički izložbeni prostor. <br></p>', '43.859662182976656', '18.4288090467453', 'Kuršumlija medresa je visoka vjerska škola, Gazi Husrev-begova zadužbina iz 1537. godine, posvećena dobrotvorovoj majci Seldžuki, kćerki sultana Bajazita II. U svoje vrijeme bila je pandan najpoznatijim evropskim univerzitetima.', 2203, '92,1,97', 1, 'Škola,Baščaršija,Čaršija,Istorija,Obrazovanje', 38, 15, '33', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'kursumlija medresa', '#skola,#bascarsija,#carsija,#istorija,#obrazovanje', 'kur&scaron;umlija medresa je visoka vjerska &scaron;kola, gazi husrev-begova zaduzbina iz 1537. godine, posvecena dobrotvorovoj majci seldzuki, kcerki sultana bajazita ii. u svoje vrijeme bila je pandan najpoznatijim evropskim univerzitetima.', 1, 'Kursumlija Madrasah', 'kuršumlija-medresa-en', '<p></p>Kursumlija Madrasah is the Secondary Islamic School.It was built in 1537\n as one of the Ghazi Husrev-Bey’s endowments and is dedicated to his \nmother, Selçuka, a Turkish princess and a daughter of Sultan Bayezid II.&nbsp;<div><br><div>At the time, it was one of the best European universities. People called\n it "Kursumlija” (due to its lead roof; tur. kursum - lead). The \nMadrasah reflects a magnificent design of that period, with central \natrium surrounded by porches, pillars and twelve classrooms (tur. \ndershana - classroom). Each room is under a dome and has its own \nfireplace. A fountain decorates the Hellenistic courtyard, and the \nentire structure serves as an art exhibitions venue.&nbsp;<br><p><br></p></div></div>', 'Kursumlija Madrasah is the Secondary Islamic School.', 'kursumlija madrasah', 'kursumlija medresa je visoka vjerska skola, gazi husrev-begova zaduzbina iz 1537. godine, posvecena dobrotvorovoj majci seldzuki, kcerki sultana bajazita ii. u svoje vrijeme bila je pandan najpoznatijim evropskim univerzitetima.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3532, 'Hanikah', 'hanikah', 91, 1558, '<p>Hanikah (perz. hanikah – tekija s internatom za derviše) je izgrađen 1531. godine, prvobitno kao pravougaoni objekt sa 14 kabineta i simahanom, prostorijom u kojoj se obavlja derviški obred zvani zikr. </p><p>Bila je to lijepa građevina s atrijem ispod stupova, dvorištem i šadrvanom. Hanikah je više puta stradao u požarima i obnavljan, a gotovo u potpunosti je nestao 1931. godine, kada je građena zgrada nove medrese, kasnijeg Islamskog fakulteta. <br> <br> Po uzoru na prvobitnu građevinu, Hanikah je iznova izgrađen 2000. godine. Dodan je jedino pokretni stakleni krov koji pokriva unutrašnje dvorište. <br></p>', '43.85964284319759', '18.429114818572998', 'Hanikah (perz. hanikah – tekija s internatom za derviše) je izgrađen 1531. godine, prvobitno kao pravougaoni objekt sa 14 kabineta i simahanom, prostorijom u kojoj se obavlja derviški obred zvani zikr.', 2203, '175,8,97', 1, 'Baščaršija,Čaršija,Istorija,#Atrakcija', 59, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'hanikah', '', 'hanikah (perz. hanikah – tekija s internatom za dervise) je izgraden 1531. godine, prvobitno kao pravougaoni objekt sa 14 kabineta i simahanom, prostorijom u kojoj se obavlja derviski obred zvani zikr.', 1, 'Hanikah', 'hanikah-en', '<p>Hanikah (perz. hanikah – Dervis tekke) was built in 1531 as a \nrectangle-shaped building with 14 study rooms and simahana (room used \nfor a dervish religious ritual called "zikr”).&nbsp;It was a beautiful atrium edifice with pillars, inner yard and a fountain.&nbsp;<br></p><p>The Hanikah was severely damaged in frequent fires that struck Sarajevo \nin the past. It ceased to exist in 1931, when a new Madrasah building \nwas erected. It was rebuilt in 2000. The present-day edifice is a \nreplica of the old one, with the exception of a glazed roof which was \nadded.&nbsp;<br></p>', 'Hanikah (perz. hanikah – Dervis tekke) was built in 1531 as a rectangle-shaped building with 14 study rooms and simahana (room used for a dervish religious ritual called "zikr”).', 'hanikah', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3533, 'Gazi Husrev-begov bezistan', 'gazi-husrev-begov-bezistan', 91, 481, '<p></p>Gazi Husrev-begov bezistan je građen u etapama između 1537. i 1555. godine, kao drugi sarajevski bezistan iz Gazi Husrev-begove zadužbine.<div><br><div>Pravougaonog je oblika, dug 109 metara, sa zasvođenom unutrašnjom ulicom, prvobitno pokriven olovom. Bezistan ima tri ulaza, jedan iz Gazi Husrev-begove ulice i po jedan iz ulica Ferhadija i Zelenih beretki. Gazi-husrev begov bezistan je poznat i kao „Dugi bezistan“ i služi kao trgovački prostor.  <br><p><br></p></div></div>', '43.85878221667815', '18.428066074848175', 'Gazi Husrev-begov bezistan je građen u etapama između 1537. i 1555. godine, kao drugi sarajevski bezistan iz Gazi Husrev-begove zadužbine.', 746, '-31,-13,107', 1, '#Baščaršija,#Čaršija,#Istorija,#Atrakcija', 81, 15, '13', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'gazi husrev-begov bezistan', '', 'gazi husrev-begov bezistan je graden u etapama izmedu 1537. i 1555. godine, kao drugi sarajevski bezistan iz gazi husrev-begove zaduzbine.', 1, 'Ghazi Husrev-Beys Bedestan ', 'gazi-husrev-begov-bezistan-en', '<p></p>Ghazi Husrev-Beys Bedestan (Bazaar) was built in several stages between \n1537 and 1555. This was the second bedestan built from Ghazi \nHusrev-Bey’s endowment. It is a rectangle shaped structure, 109 meters \nlong, with a barrel vault.&nbsp;<div>This was the second bedestan built from Ghazi Husrev-Bey’s endowment. It\n is a rectangle shaped structure, 109 meters long, with a barrel vault. \nIt was originally covered in lead. There are four entrances into the \nBedestan. It is a trading bazaar and often referred to as "the long \nbedestan”.&nbsp;</div>', 'Ghazi Husrev-Beys Bedestan (Bazaar) was built in several stages between 1537 and 1555.', 'ghazi husrev-beys bedestan', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3534, 'Slatko ćoše', 'slatko-ćoše', 91, 1558, '<p>Dobilo je ime po slastičarnama koje se od davnina nalaze na ovome mjestu. Upravo na ovom prostoru napravljen je koncem 19. stoljeća nagao arhitektonski rez u srcu starog Sarajeva, pa je na tom gradskom raskrižju golim okom... <br></p><p>...vidljiv susret dviju civilizacija, tradicija, kultura, navika življenja i stanovanja. Ovdje su se dolaskom Austro-Ugarske monarhije u Bosnu i u Sarajevo susreli i doslovce dotaknuli Istok i Zapad. Staro Sarajevo se protezalo i dalje, preko dvjestotinjak metara udaljenog Gazi Husrev-begovog hamama, pa sve do Magribije džamije na Marijin-Dvoru, dobra dva kilometra nizvodno. <br> <br> Ovdje, međutim, završava 16. stoljeće i zlatno doba Sarajeva – vrijeme u kojem je podignuto više od 100 džamija, preko 300 dućana, šest tekija, sedam hamama, više medresa, biblioteka, mostova, hanova, karavan-saraja... <br></p>', '43.85929666009108', '18.42820018529892', 'Dobilo je ime po slastičarnama koje se od davnina nalaze na ovome mjestu. Upravo na ovom prostoru napravljen je koncem 19. stoljeća nagao arhitektonski rez u srcu starog Sarajeva, pa je na tom gradskom raskrižju golim okom...', 753, '148,6,107', 1, 'Baščaršija,#Atrakcija ,#Istorija,#Čaršija', 71, 15, '2', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'slatko cose', '#kafic,#bascarsija,#carape,#pice,#kafa,#sok,#basta,#limunada', 'dobilo je ime po slasticarnama koje se od davnina nalaze na ovome mjestu. upravo na ovom prostoru napravljen je koncem 19. stoljeca nagao arhitektonski rez u srcu starog sarajeva, pa je na tom gradskom raskrizju golim okom...', 1, 'Slatko cose – Sweet Corner Where East Meets West', 'slatko-ćoše-en', '<p></p>Slatko cose was named after the tiny pastry shops that have been there \nfor over centuries. On this exact spot is where the old Ottoman Sarajevo\n suddenly starts to flow into the Austro-Hungarian period.&nbsp;<div></div><div>With the Austro-Hungarians a new life style, new architecture, and a new\n stream of thought was born. Yet, even though it is visible to the naked\n eye, this crossroad of the old and the new is merely a subtle \nencounter. The Ottoman heritage is visible in other spots as well, \nlocated a few kilometers from this site (Ghazi Husrev-Bey’s Hamam or \nMagribija Mosque). However, this border announces the end of the 16th \ncentury and the golden era during which over a hundred mosques, three \nhundred shops, six tekkes, seven hamam baths, several madrasah schools, \nlibraries, bridges, inns and caravanserai were built.&nbsp;<br></div>', 'Slatko cose was named after the tiny pastry shops that have been there for over centuries.', 'slatko cose', 'dobilo je ime po slasticarnama koje se od davnina nalaze na ovome mjestu. upravo na ovom prostoru napravljen je koncem 19. stoljeca nagao arhitektonski rez u srcu starog sarajeva, pa je na tom gradskom raskrizju golim okom...', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3535, 'At-mejdan', 'at-mejdan', 91, 1292, '<p></p>U najstarijem periodu Sarajeva ovo je bio trg roblja i mjesto izvršenja smrtnih kazni vješanjem, po čemu je u narodu prozvan Sijaset-mejdan (tur. siyaset – kazna).<div>Naziv At-mejdan je iz kasnijeg perioda, po konjskoj pijaci i hipodromu. U 16. stoljeću tu je izgrađena džamija i mekteb, a u 17. medresa i biblioteka, ali su svi ti objekti porušeni u 19. stoljeću, kada je austrougarska uprava započela urbanizaciju Sarajeva. <br> <br> U središnjem dijelu At-mejdana 1911. godine izgrađen je, po projektu arhitekte Josipa Pospišila, Muzički paviljon s kafanom. Trg je projektiran kao park sa zasadima zelenila, klupama i stazama za šetnju. Tu je praznicima svirala vojna limena glazba. Paviljon je srušen prilikom njemačkog bombardiranja Sarajeva 1941. godine, te je danas ponovo obnovljen i predstavlja mali gradski park s kafanom, a nedavno je izvršena i restauracija starog mezarja i izgrađena manja džamija na mjestu one prijašnje iz osmanlijskog perioda.<br> <br> Na ovom području je osnivač Sarajeva Isa-beg Ishaković izgradio i svoje upravno središte, dvor (saraj), po kome je grad dobio ime (Saraj-ovasi; tur. saraj – dvor, i ovasi – polje), 1454/1455. godine, a krajem osmanlijske uprave ovdje je od 1854. do 1856. godine izgrađena kasarna koja i danas služi kao namjenski objekt.  <br><p><br></p></div>', '43.857047387936554', '18.42831015586853', 'U najstarijem periodu Sarajeva ovo je bio trg roblja i mjesto izvršenja smrtnih kazni vješanjem, po čemu je u narodu prozvan Sijaset-mejdan (tur. siyaset – kazna).', 958, '-75,-1,107', 1, '#Baščaršija,#Čaršija,#Istorija,#Atrakcija', 147, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'at-mejdan', '', 'u najstarijem periodu sarajeva ovo je bio trg roblja i mjesto izvrsenja smrtnih kazni vjesanjem, po cemu je u narodu prozvan sijaset-mejdan (tur. siyaset – kazna).', 1, 'At Mejdan ', 'at-mejdan-en', '<p></p>In the past this area was known as the Sijaset mejdan (tur. siyaset – \npunishment), a trade slave square and a place where death penalties by \nhanging were executed. The name At Mejdan derives from a later period \nafter a horse market and hippodrome.<div><p></p></div><div>A mosque and a maktab (Islamic primary school) were built on this site \nin the 16th century, and a madrasah and a library in the 17th century. \nWith the arrival of the Austro-Hungarian Monarchy, all the buildings \nwere ruined (19th c.).<br>\n<br>\nThe Music Pavilion with a cafe designed by Josip Pospisil was erected in\n 1911. The pavilion was surrounded by a wonderful tiny park with walking\n paths and benches. Holidays were always announced with a brass-band \nplaying at the Music Pavilion. The Pavilion was destroyed during the \nSecond World War bombing in 1941, and was restored into a small park \nwith a cafe. The old Muslim graveyard was renovated as well and a small \nmosque built at the site of a former mosque. <br>\n<br>\nIn this area, Isa-Bey Ishakovic, a founder of Sarajevo, built his \nadministration seat, a court to which the city owns its name (tur. saray\n – court; ovasi – field) in 1454/1455. At the end of the Ottoman rule, \nthey started building a barracks in 1854. The barracks was completed in \n1856 and it has been used as such ever since.<br></div>', 'In the past this area was known as the Sijaset mejdan (tur. siyaset – punishment), a trade slave square and a place where death penalties by hanging were executed.', 'at mejdan', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3536, 'Konak', 'konak-konaci-bb', 91, 990, '<p>Rezidencija osmanlijskih namjesnika u Bosni izgrađena 1868. godine u stilu kasnog baroka za stolovanja vezira Topal Šerif Osman-paše.<br></p><p>Izgrađen je na temelju prvog dvora (tur. saray; 15. st.) po kojem je grad dobio ime. Nakon austrougarske okupacije Bosne i Hercegovine, Konak postaje jedan od prvih sarajevskih objekata koje vlasti restauriraju za svoje potrebe. Ovdje su od 1878. do 1918. godine odsjedali članovi kuće Habsburg, od 1918. do 1941. generali, banovi i župani, a u novoj Jugoslaviji političari iz mnogih zemalja svijeta. <br> <br> Austrougarski car Franjo Josip I boravio je u Konaku četiri dana za vrijeme posjete Sarajevu maja 1910. godine. Iz Konaka su put Beča ispraćeni i posmrtni ostaci austrougarskog prestolonasljednika Franje Ferdinanda i njegove supruge Sofije, ubijenih u Sarajevu hicima Gavrila Principa 28. juna 1914. godine.  <br></p>', '43.85631630786513', '18.430745601654053', 'Rezidencija osmanlijskih namjesnika u Bosni izgrađena 1868. godine u stilu kasnog baroka za stolovanja vezira Topal Šerif Osman-paše.', 948, '-82,4,107', 1, '#Baščaršija,#Čaršija,#Istorija,#Atrakcija', 96, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'konak', '', 'rezidencija osmanlijskih namjesnika u bosni izgradena 1868. godine u stilu kasnog baroka za stolovanja vezira topal serif osman-pase.', 1, 'Konak', 'konak-konaci-bb-en', '<p>Konak is an Ottoman governors’ residence built in 1868 in Late Baroque \nstyle during the rule of Topal Osman Pasha, an Ottoman vizier. It was \nbuilt on a site of the former Konak (tur. saray – court; 15th c.) to \nwhich the city owes its name.<br></p><p>During the Austro-Hungarian occupation the building was adapted for the \nneeds of the government and the military. From 1878 to 1918 the Konak \nwas the residence of the Habsburg family, and during the Yugoslav \nRepublic (1918 to 1941) it was used by generals, governors and \ndistrict-prefects, and many politicians from around the world. <br>\n<br>\nThe Austro-Hungarian Emperor Franz Josef resided in Konak during his \nvisit in May, 1910. Franz Ferdinand, the Austro-Hungarian Archduke, died\n here after he was fatally wounded by Gavrilo Princip’s shot on June 28,\n 1914. <br>\n<br>\nToday, it is a state residence used by the members of the Presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina.<br></p>', 'Konak is an Ottoman governors’ residence built in 1868 in Late Baroque style during the rule of Topal Osman Pasha, an Ottoman vizier.', 'konak', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3537, 'Muzej XIV zimskih olimpijskih igara Sarajevo 1984. u Zetri', 'muzej-xiv-zimskih-olimpijskih-igara-sarajevo-1984.-u-zetri', 62, 76, '<p></p>Na dan otvaranja XIV zimskih olimpijskih igara u Sarajevu, u predivnom ambijentu Mandića vile otvoren je i Olimpijski muzej. Zgrada je teško devastirana tokom opsade i granatiranja Sarajeva 1992-1995. godine...&nbsp;<div>...pri čemu je u najvećoj mjeri stradala i postavka muzeja, da bi ova institucija bila ponovo otvorena na 20. godišnjicu održavanja Igara, ovoga puta u prostorijama Olimpijskog komiteta Bosne i Hercegovine u Zetri. <br> <br> Muzej posjeduje dokumentarnu postavku o organizaciji, pripremi i realizaciji ZOI ''84 i umjetničku kolekciju doniranih djela umjetnika s područja bivše Jugoslavije, slikara, grafičara i kipara.<br><p><br></p></div>', '43.87136159933803', '18.40907335281372', 'Na dan otvaranja XIV zimskih olimpijskih igara u Sarajevu, u predivnom ambijentu Mandića vile otvoren je i Olimpijski muzej. Zgrada je teško devastirana tokom opsade i granatiranja Sarajeva 1992-1995. godine...', 0, '', 1, '#Muzej,#Istorija,#Atrakcija ,#Olimpijada', 46, 15, 'bb', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, '', '', '', 1, 'Olympic Museum', 'muzej-xiv-zimskih-olimpijskih-igara-sarajevo-1984.-u-zetri-en', '<p>The Olympic Museum opened its doors on the occasion of the 14th Winter \nOlympic Games on February 7th, 1984. It was located at the Mandic Villa,\n a beautiful building severely damaged during the 1992-1995 war. \nMajority of the collection was ruined along with the building, and the \nremaining transferred to the Zetra Olympic Hall, when the museum was \nreopened on the 20th anniversary of the 14th WOG. <br>\n<br>\nThe museum features documents about the event preparation, organization \nand implementation, paintings, graphic art, sculptures and photos \ncelebrating the 14th Winter Olympic Games held in Sarajevo in 1984.<br></p>', 'The Olympic Museum opened its doors on the occasion of the 14th Winter Olympic Games on February 7th, 1984.', 'olympic museum', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3538, 'Muzej književnosti i pozorišne umjetnosti – Galerija ˝Mak˝', 'muzej-književnosti-i-pozorišne-umjetnosti-–-galerija-˝mak˝', 62, 1582, '<p>Osnovan 1961. godine kao Muzej književnosti, od 1969. godine počinje izučavati i pozorišnu umjetnost Bosne i Hercegovine. Smješten je u kući iz sredine 19. stoljeća, nekada vlasništvo pravoslavne trgovačke porodice Skarić (kasnije porodice Despić), u ulici Sime Milutinovića Sarajlije (naziv nosi po velikom pjesniku, historičaru i avanturisti). <br> <br> U prizemlju je likovna galerija „Mak". Ispred kuće je lijepo dvorište, odvojeno od ulice visokim zidom. Bogati fond muzeja sačinjavaju rukopisi, prepiske, lični dokumenti, predmeti, fotografije stvaralaca i njihovih saradnika, listovi, časopisi, publikacije, knjige u kojima su pisci objavljivali svoje radove, zatim pozorišni plakati, programi, scenske i individualne fotografije, scenske i kostimografske skice i drugo.<br> <br> Građa je raspoređena u zbirke – 67 književnih i 17 pozorišnih, s više od 20.000 eksponata.  <br></p>', '43.85769336128138', '18.426754474639893', 'Osnovan 1961. godine kao Muzej književnosti, od 1969. godine počinje izučavati i pozorišnu umjetnost Bosne i Hercegovine. Smješten je u kući iz sredine 19. stoljeća, nekada vlasništvo pravoslavne trgovačke porodice Skarić (kasnije porodice Despić), u ulic', 433, '-193,0,107', 1, '#Muzej,#Istorija,#Baščaršija,#Čaršija,#Galerija', 41, 15, '7', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'muzej knjizevnosti i pozorisne umjetnosti – galerija ˝mak˝', '', 'osnovan 1961. godine kao muzej knjizevnosti, od 1969. godine pocinje izucavati i pozorisnu umjetnost bosne i hercegovine. smjesten je u kuci iz sredine 19. stoljeca, nekada vlasnistvo pravoslavne trgovacke porodice skaric (kasnije porodice despic), u ulic', 1, '˝Mak˝ Gallery', 'muzej-književnosti-i-pozorišne-umjetnosti-–-galerija-˝mak˝-en', '<p>Operating since 1992, Mak Gallery is located on the ground floor of the \nMuseum of Literature and Theatre Arts of Bosnia and Herzegovina.&nbsp;<br></p>', 'Operating since 1992, Mak Gallery is located on the ground floor of the Museum of Literature and Theatre Arts of Bosnia and Herzegovina. ', 'gallery "mak"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3539, 'Muzeji i galerije Spomenički kompleks ˝Tunel spasa˝', 'muzeji-i-galerije-spomenički-kompleks-˝tunel-spasa˝', 62, 857, '<p><p>Tokom opsade Sarajeva 1992-1995. izgrađen je tunel kojim su spojene dvije slobodne teritorije. Tunel je prokopan i otvoren 1993. godine ispod Sarajevskog aerodroma, nadljudskim naporima učesnika ovoga jedinstvenog poduhvata. Kako je spajao naselja Dobrinju i Butmir, tunel je tako i šifriran: Objekat D-B. Tunel je dug oko 720 metara, a visok oko 1,5 metara. Tokom 1994. kroz tunel su postavljene minijaturne šine s malim metalnim vagonima, što je znatno olakšavalo svaki transport. </p> <p>Tunelom je u Sarajevo dopremana humanitarna pomoć, preko Igmana su iz Sarajeva evakuirani najteži ranjenici i pojedini strani političari te slavne ličnosti poput Susan Sontag, koji su davali podršku opkoljenom Sarajevu. Danas je tunel jedinstveno muzejsko zdanje i jedna od najposjećenijih turističkih atrakcija u gradu.</p><br></p>', '43.820171', '18.336878', 'Tokom opsade Sarajeva 1992-1995. izgrađen je tunel kojim su spojene dvije slobodne teritorije.', 0, '', 1, '#Muzej,#Istorija,#Atrakcija', 73, 15, '1', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, '', '', '', 1, 'Monumental Complex „Tunnel of Salvation“', 'muzeji-i-galerije-spomenički-kompleks-˝tunel-spasa˝-en', 'The war tunnel was constructed during the 1425-day long siege of Sarajevo (1992 to 1995 siege), to connect two free territories. The entrance and exit of the tunnel are two houses situated at the opposite sides of the airport. Thus, the tunnel connected Dobrinja and Butmir settlements, and was named "Objekat D-B”. Tunnel construction was initiated in 1993 and completed the same year. The tunnel is 720 meters long, 1.50 meters high. In 1994, narrow rails and mine carts were added to facilitate transportation of food and medicine.\n\nHumanitarian aid was delivered through this tunnel, and wounded soldiers sent out of Sarajevo over Igman mountain. Politicians and world-known reporters such as Susan Sontag used this tunnel to come to Sarajevo and offer their support to the war-torn city. Today, this unique museum structure is one of the most popular tourist attractions in the city.', 'The war tunnel was constructed during the 1425-day long siege of Sarajevo (1992 to 1995 siege), to connect two free territories.', 'monumental complex "tunel of salvation"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3540, 'Galerija ˝11/07/95˝', 'galerija-˝11-07-95˝', 96, 1876, '<p></p><p></p>Prva memorijalna galerija u Bosni i Hercegovini sa izložbenim prostorom kojem je cilj očuvati sjećanja na tragediju Srebrenice i 8372 osobe tragično stradale u srebreničkom genocidu.<br><p></p>', '43.85930052806986', '18.425748646259308', 'Prva memorijalna galerija u Bosni i Hercegovini sa izložbenim prostorom kojem je cilj očuvati sjećanja na tragediju Srebrenice i 8372 osobe tragično stradale u srebreničkom genocidu.', 464, '158,-4,107', 1, '#Galerija,#Istorija,#Srebrenica', 28, 15, '2', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'galerija ˝11/07/95˝', '', 'prva memorijalna galerija u bosni i hercegovini sa izlozbenim prostorom kojem je cilj ocuvati sjecanja na tragediju srebrenice i 8372 osobe tragicno stradale u srebrenickom genocidu.', 1, 'Gallery ˝11/07/95˝', 'galerija-˝11-07-95˝-en', '<p></p><p>Gallery 11/07/95 is the first memorial gallery in Bosnia and Herzegovina\n - an exhibition space aiming to preserve the memory of the Srebrenica \nGenocide and the 8372 persons who tragically lost their lives in the \ngenocide.</p>', 'Gallery 11/07/95 is the first memorial gallery in Bosnia and Herzegovina - an exhibition space aiming to preserve the memory of the Srebrenica Genocide and the 8372 persons who tragically lost their lives in the genocide.', 'gallery "11/07/95"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3541, 'Galerija ˝Boris Smoje˝', 'galerija-˝boris-smoje˝', 5, 1458, '<p>Mala kafe galerija u Centru Sarajeva.<br></p>', '43.85726593658801', '18.41729700565338', 'Mala kafe galerija u Centru Sarajeva.', 702, '7,2,78', 1, '#Kafić,#Galerija,#Bašta,#Kafa,#Sok,#Pivo,#Izložba', 53, 15, '11', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'galerija ˝boris smoje˝', '', 'mala kafe galerija u centru sarajeva.', 1, '˝Boris Smoje˝ Gallery', 'galerija-˝boris-smoje˝-en', '<p></p><p>Small cafe gallery in the center of Sarajevo.</p>', 'Small cafe gallery in the center of Sarajevo.', 'gallery "boris smoje"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3542, 'Galerija ˝Roman Petrović˝', 'galerija-˝roman-petrović˝', 96, 1129, '<p>Galerija izlaže skulpture, fotografije i likovna umjetnost. <br></p>', '43.85820394603923', '18.42106282711029', 'Galerija izlaže skulpture, fotografije i likovna umjetnost.', 0, '', 1, 'Galerija,Umjetnost', 66, 15, '54', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'galerija ˝roman petrovic˝', '#galerija,#umjetnost', 'galerija izlaze skulpture, fotografije i likovna umjetnost.', 1, '˝Roman Petrovic˝ Gallery', 'galerija-˝roman-petrović˝-en', '<p></p><p>The Roman Petrovic Gallery features sculptures, photography and paintings.&nbsp;</p>', ' The Roman Petrovic Gallery features sculptures, photography and paintings. ', 'gallery ˝roman petrovic˝', 'galerija izlaze skulpture, fotografije i likovna umjetnost.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3543, 'Collegium Artisticum', 'collegium-artisticum', 96, 1689, '<p><p>  Veoma zanimljiva kolekcija fotografija, slika i grafika.  </p><br></p>', '43.85462009021419', '18.41487228870392', 'Veoma zanimljiva kolekcija fotografija, slika i grafika.', 827, '188,4,107', 1, '#Galerija,#Izložba,#Kultura,#Umjetnost', 41, 15, 'bb', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'collegium artisticum', '', 'veoma zanimljiva kolekcija fotografija, slika i grafika.', 1, 'Collegium Artisticum', 'collegium-artisticum-en', '<p></p>Houses very interesting collections of photography, painting and graphic art.', 'Veoma zanimljiva kolekcija fotografija, slika i grafika.', 'collegium artisticum', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3544, 'Vilsonovo šetalište', 'vilsonovo-šetalište', 69, 851, '<p></p><p></p>Aleja u Vilsonovom šetalištu uz rijeku Miljacku zasađena je još u vremenu austrougarske vladavine stablima kestena i lipe, koja svojim masivnim krošnjama ljeti stvaraju prijatan hlad. <br><p></p><div>U poslijepodnevnim satima šetalište se zatvara za saobraćaj, te ljubitelji prirode mogu uživati u šetnji i ćaskanju na klupama pored Miljacke ili u vožnji bicikla.    <br></div>', '43.853596920776425', '18.398054838180542', 'Aleja u Vilsonovom šetalištu uz rijeku Miljacku zasađena je još u vremenu austrougarske vladavine stablima kestena i lipe, koja svojim masivnim krošnjama ljeti stvaraju prijatan hlad.', 0, '', 1, 'Atrakcija ,Park,#Priroda,#šetalište', 130, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'vilsonovo setaliste', '#atrakcija ,#park', 'aleja u vilsonovom &scaron;etali&scaron;tu uz rijeku miljacku zasadena je jo&scaron; u vremenu austrougarske vladavine stablima kestena i lipe, koja svojim masivnim kro&scaron;njama ljeti stvaraju prijatan hlad.', 1, 'Vilson’s Promenade', 'vilsonovo-šetalište-en', '<p></p>Vilson’s Promenade is one of the major gathering places for people of \nall ages in the afternoon hours. It is a long tree-lined alley in the \nmid of the city which turns into the main outdoor spot after the street \nis closed for traffic.<div></div><div>Skating, bicycle riding, jogging or just a simple chat with friends is \nmore than enjoyable in the shade of chestnut and plane trees.&nbsp;<br></div>', 'Vilson’s Promenade is one of the major gathering places for people of all ages in the afternoon hours.', 'vilsonovo setaliste', 'aleja u vilsonovom setalistu uz rijeku miljacku zasadena je jos u vremenu austrougarske vladavine stablima kestena i lipe, koja svojim masivnim krosnjama ljeti stvaraju prijatan hlad.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3545, 'Pionirska dolina', 'pionirska-dolina', 69, 1367, '<p></p><p></p>Pionirska dolina je parkovni prostor kroz koji protječe Koševski potok i u kojem je do rata 1992-1995. godine bio smješten rekreacioni centar (zabavni park i zoološki vrt).<div>Danas Pionirsku dolinu najčešće posjećuju mališani, koji uživaju u upoznavanju sa životinjama i igri u Drvenom gradu.&nbsp;<br><div><br></div></div>', '43.87884028735443', '18.41212034225464', 'Pionirska dolina je parkovni prostor kroz koji protječe Koševski potok i u kojem je do rata 1992-1995. godine bio smješten rekreacioni centar (zabavni park i zoološki vrt).', 0, '', 1, '#Zoološki vrt,#Park,#Životinje', 109, 15, '58', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, '', '', '', 1, 'Pionirska dolina', 'pionirska-dolina-en', '<p></p>Pionirska dolina is a zoological and entertainment park for children. \nThe park covers a large area with the Kosevo Brook running through \nPionirska dolina. &nbsp;<div>Learning about animals, playing on the Wooden Castle or doing other \nrecreational activities with your children can be a lot of fun for the \nwhole family. &nbsp;</div>', 'Pionirska dolina is a zoological and entertainment park for children.', 'pionirska dolina', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3546, 'Vodopad Skakavac', 'vodopad-skakavac', 91, 1880, '<p></p><p></p>Vodopad Skakavac se nalazi 12 kilometara sjeverno od Sarajeva, iznad sela Nahoreva. Visok je 98 metara, što ga čini drugim vodopadom po visini u Evropi.<div>Ovaj kraj predstavlja izazov za šetače rekreativce, bicikliste, trkače, speleologe, penjače, fotografe, sakupljače gljiva ili ljekovitog bilja. <br> <br> Na prostoru oko vodopada zabilježeno je preko 1500 vrsta biljaka, od kojih su neke ljekovite, endemske ili veoma rijetke. Šume smrče, jele i bukve kriju brojne gljive, zečeve, kune, ptice, ali i vukove, medvjede, lisice...<br> <br> Vodopad i šire područje oko njega proglašen je spomenikom prirode.<br><div><div><br></div></div></div>', '43.941911589779174', '18.45351219177246', 'Vodopad Skakavac se nalazi 12 kilometara sjeverno od Sarajeva, iznad sela Nahoreva. Visok je 98 metara, &scaron;to ga čini drugim vodopadom po visini u Evropi.', 0, '', 1, 'vodopad,Priroda,Atrakcija', 107, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'vodopad skakavac', '#vodopad,#atrakcija ,#izlet,#izletiste,#priroda,#prirodno nasljede', 'vodopad skakavac se nalazi 12 kilometara sjeverno od sarajeva, iznad sela nahoreva. visok je 98 metara, sto ga cini drugim vodopadom po visini u evropi.', 1, 'Skakavac Waterfall', 'vodopad-skakavac-en', '<p></p>Skakavac Waterfall is located 12 km north of Sarajevo, above the \nNahorevo Village. It is a 98-m high waterfall, the second tallest in \nEurope.<div>It is a part of a Natural Park and it takes a 3-hour thrilling walk \nthrough the fir, beech, spruce, and ash tree forest. The waterfall is \nsurrounded by endemic flora and fauna species and is great for mushroom \nand medicinal herbs picking. It is an oasis of peace and relaxation for \nall nature lovers, athletes, mountain bikers, photographers, hikers… &nbsp;<br><div><p><br></p></div></div>', 'Skakavac Waterfall is located 12 km north of Sarajevo, above the Nahorevo Village. ', 'skakavac waterfall', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3547, 'Barice i Čavljak', 'barice-i-čavljak', 69, 146, '<p></p><p></p>Devet kilometara od Sarajeva nalaze se dva veoma popularna izletišta – Barice i Čavljak. Od Čavljaka se pružaju uređene planinarske staze prema planinskim vrhovima Crepoljsko (1524 m)...<div><br></div><div>...za oko sat hoda, Bukovik (1534 m) za oko sat i po hoda, ili vodopad Skakavac (1136 m) S Bukovika se možete spustiti na Skakavac za oko 45 minuta hoda. Na Baricama, Čavljaku, Crepoljskom i Bukoviku nalazi se nekoliko planinarskih domova, a na Crepoljskom, pored Lovačkog doma, ima i nekoliko eko sela – Radonja (Borin Dol), Vučija Luka i Eco futura. &nbsp;<br><div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div>', '43.89159906671626', '18.44518661499023', 'Devet kilometara od Sarajeva nalaze se dva veoma popularna izleti&amp;scaron;ta &amp;ndash; Barice i Čavljak. Od Čavljaka se pružaju uređene planinarske staze prema planinskim vrhovima Crepoljsko (1524 m)...', 0, '', 1, 'Izlet,Izletište,Park,Priroda', 108, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'barice i cavljak', 'izlet,izletiste,park,priroda', 'devet kilometara od sarajeva nalaze se dva veoma popularna izleti&scaron;ta &ndash; barice i cavljak. od cavljaka se pruzaju uredene planinarske staze prema planinskim vrhovima crepoljsko (1524 m)...', 1, 'Barice and Cavljak', 'barice-i-čavljak-en', '<p></p>Barice and Cavljak are outdoor spots located 9 km from the city center. \nBoth are ideal for a family day out, lunch or recreational activities. \nCavljak extends towards Bukovik (1,5 hour walk, 1534 m),&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.45em; background-color: initial;">Crepoljsko (1 hour walk, 1524 m) and the Skakavac Waterfall (1136 m).</span><div>\n<br>\nThe mountain trail from Bukovik to Skakavac Waterfall is popular as well\n and it takes approximately 45 minutes to reach the waterfall. There are\n several mountain huts at Barice, Cavljak, Bukovik and Crepoljsko (at \nCrepoljsko you can also visit the Hunters'' Hut and a few villages \nRadonja-Borin Dol, Vucija Luka or Ecofutura).&nbsp;<br></div>', 'Barice and Cavljak are outdoor spots located 9 km from the city center. Both are ideal for a family day out, lunch or recreational activities. Cavljak extends towards Bukovik (1,5 hour walk, 1534 m)... ', 'barice and cavljak', 'devet kilometara od sarajeva nalaze se dva veoma popularna izletista – barice i cavljak. od cavljaka se pruzaju uredene planinarske staze prema planinskim vrhovima crepoljsko (1524 m)...', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3548, 'Šetalište Dariva', 'šetalište-dariva', 91, 320, '<p></p><p></p>Na staroj cesti koja od gradskog bazena (u narodu poznat kao Bentbaša) vodi uz Miljacku istočno prema Darivi i Kozijoj ćupriji, danas pješačkom prostoru i biciklističkoj stazi&nbsp;dugoj osam kilometara, nalazi se aleja mladih stabala – Aleja ambasadora, gdje stabla sade znameniti posjetitelji Sarajeva. Do sada je duž šetališta lipe posadilo 163 ambasadora. Uz šetalište se nalaze klupe za odmor i mjesta za roštiljanje. Poslije izlaska iz starog austrijskog tunela šetaču se pred očima ukaže visoka tanka špicasta stijena, poznata kao Babin zub. U austrijskim izvorima spominje se kao Kleopatrina igla. Ovdje, profesionalni penjači i iskusni avanturisti okušavaju svoje vještine.&nbsp;<br> <br> Na kraju šetnice stižete do Kozije ćuprije, jednog od najstarijih i najljepših sarajevskih mostova, izgrađene u 16. stoljeću na carskom drumu koji je nekada vodio do Istanbula. Vjeruje se da je most zadužbina Mehmed-paše Sokolovića, velikog vezira iz 16. stoljeća. &nbsp; &nbsp;<div><div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div>', '43.85869131832045', '18.43929648399353', 'Na staroj cesti koja od gradskog bazena (u narodu poznat kao Bentba&scaron;a) vodi uz Miljacku istočno prema Darivi i Kozijoj ćupriji, danas pje&scaron;ačkom prostoru i biciklističkoj stazi...', 0, '', 1, 'šetalište,Priroda,Izlet,prirodno nasljeđe', 108, 15, '', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'setaliste dariva', '#setaliste,#priroda,#izlet,#prirodno nasljede', 'na staroj cesti koja od gradskog bazena (u narodu poznat kao bentbasa) vodi uz miljacku istocno prema darivi i kozijoj cupriji, danas pjesackom prostoru i biciklistickoj stazi...', 1, 'Dariva Promenade', 'šetalište-dariva-en', '<p></p>The old road stretching from the city pool (locally known as Bentbasa) \nup the Miljacka River leads towards Dariva and Kozija cuprija Bridge \n(Goat’s Bridge).<div><br><div>It is an 8-km walking and bicycle riding trail. The first section of the\n Promenade is the Ambassadors’ Alley, where a new sprout is planted in \nthe honor of every new ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina. Up to \ntoday, there are 163 trees. You can rest on one of the benches along the\n river bank or choose one of the barbecue sites and have a perfect day \nout with your friends and family.<br>\n<br>\nAfter you pass the Austro-Hungarian tunnel you will see a tall pointy \nrock "Babin zub” (mentioned under the name "Cleopatra’s Pin” in \nAustro-Hungarian documents). Often, you will encounter professional rock\n climbers and adventurers showing off their climbing skills as you walk \nby. The Dariva Promenade ends with Kozija cuprija Bridge built in the \nfirst half of 16th century on the famous Istanbul Road. It is one of the\n most beautiful single span stone bridges in the country, assumed to \nhave been built by the endowment of Mehmed-Pasha Sokolovic, the grand \nvizier.&nbsp;</div></div>', 'The old road stretching from the city pool (locally known as Bentbasa) up the Miljacka River leads towards Dariva and Kozija cuprija Bridge (Goat’s Bridge).', 'dariva promenade', 'na staroj cesti koja od gradskog bazena (u narodu poznat kao bentbasa) vodi uz miljacku istocno prema darivi i kozijoj cupriji, danas pjesackom prostoru i biciklistickoj stazi...', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3549, '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 'šetalište,Priroda,Izlet,prirodno nasljeđe', 0, 18, '', '0', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', '', '', 1, '', '-en', '', '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(3550, 'Hostel City Rest', 'hostel-city-rest', 40, 408, '<p>HOSTEL CITY REST SARAJEVO, we believe in hospitality as a helping profession. Through all the services we offer, we connect you directly to local Bosnian artists, craft-makers, farmers, and businessmen so that your visit to Bosnia i Herzegovina leaves a positive impact on local lives and local economy. With key partnerships and conscientious business, we promote sustainable tourism in a city that is fast rebuilding its reputation as a little piece of paradise. You can count on a comfortable bed, a clean house, a great view, and smiling staff ready to answer your questions. We welcome you to join us in a cozy hostel near Sarajevo’s center where it will be no surprise to find friends fast become family.<br></p><p>HOSTEL BEDS<br>Beds from 12€. All dorm rooms have custom-made bunks with privacy curtains, reading lights, and security lockers.<br><br>TOURS<br>From free walking tours to out-of-town excursions, our staff will connect you to high-quality local tour operators so you can learn about Sarajevo''s fascinating and complex history while enjoying its rich nature.<br><br>LOCAL CONNECTION<br>Think Bosnian hand-made souvenirs, locally-produced domestic products, seasonal fruits and vegetables from local farms, art on the walls from Sarajevo artists, and the like. We''ve got you connected!<br></p><p>We are a 4-5 minute walk from the Sarajevo Cathedral, Old Town and center.<br><br>+ From the Railway Station<br>& Main Bus Station:<br>Tram #1 leaves from directly in front of the Railway Station every 20-30 mins. Pay 1.60KM at the ticket window or 1.80KM to the tram driver, then make sure to stamp your ticket in the machines available at the front and back of the tram. Take the tram about 10-12 minutes to the ''COBANIJA'' stop. Exit the tram and turn right over bridge. Walk straight up that street and you''ll find us on the right after about 3-5 minutes walking. Taxis cost about 4€ / 8KM direct with the meter on - be careful as they often try to trick tourists into a 15KM flat fee and a fake luggage fee on top. We suggest flagging one off the street rather than taking one from the queue. If you prefer to walk the whole way, it should take you about 30-35 minutes. <br><br>+ From the East Bus Station:<br>Most buses from Serbia and Montenegro drop you off at the distant Istočno Bus Station in Republika Srpska. Public transit connections take well over 30 mins to reach the old town via bus #103, but it''s the cheapest option. Pay the driver 1.80KM for a ticket and take the bus to the stop - COBANIJA. Walk back to traffic lights and left from there we are on right side after 1-2 mins walk. A taxi direct will cost about 7€ / 15KM on the meter. Walking not recommended.<br><br>+ From the Airport: <br>At this point, taxi services pretty much have a monopoly on transportation from the Sarajevo International Airport (SJJ) and they charge over-priced flat rates to get you where you want to go. Expect to pay 15€ / 30KM at least and possibly more with luggage. We recommend instead calling other Taxi services (+387331522, +387331516, +38733760600, +38733663555) for honest rates (about 9€ / 18KM) - use your own phone or ask a friendly local. Meet them past the airport taxis in the parking lot. Alternatively, send us an email to book an airport pick-up or get advice on how to make the journey via public transit and a good little bit of walking.<br></p>', '43.85423906319336', '18.420904576778412', 'HOSTEL CITY REST SARAJEVO, we believe in hospitality as a helping profession.', 4835, '-53,0,107', 1, '#Hostel,#Smještaj,#Wi - Fi,#Recepcija,#Skladište prtljaga', 3595, 14, '6', '0', 1, 0, 4, 1, 'hostel city rest', '', 'hostel city rest sarajevo, we believe in hospitality as a helping profession.', 1, 'Hostel City Rest', 'hostel-city-rest-en', '<p>HOSTEL CITY REST SARAJEVO, we believe in hospitality as a helping profession. Through all the services we offer, we connect&nbsp;you directly to local Bos